---
import PageLayout from "@/layouts/Base";
import SocialList from "@/components/SocialList";

const meta = {
  title: "About",
  description:
    "About Sunil Pai, a product-minded systems engineer, founder, and developer-tools builder based in London.",
};
---

<PageLayout meta={meta}>
  <article class="about-page">
    <div class="grid gap-8 sm:grid-cols-[1fr_11rem] sm:items-start sm:gap-12">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">A little context</p>
        <h1 class="display-title mt-3">Hi, I’m Sunil.</h1>
        <p class="mt-6 text-xl leading-8">
          I’m a product-minded systems engineer, founder, and developer-tools builder based in
          London.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="aspect-square w-36 overflow-hidden rounded-[2rem] bg-black shadow-sm sm:w-44">
        <img
          src="/headshot-microphone.jpg"
          width="1440"
          height="1920"
          alt="Sunil Pai smiling and speaking into a microphone"
          class="h-full w-full scale-125 object-cover object-[55%_40%]"
        />
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-editorial mt-12 max-w-none">
      <p>
        I like turning new infrastructure primitives into products and abstractions that people
        can understand, adopt, and build on. My work has moved between user interfaces,
        open-source frameworks, developer platforms, stateful distributed systems, and durable
        infrastructure for AI agents.
      </p>
      <p>
        These days I’m a principal systems engineer at Cloudflare, working on agents and
        long-running AI systems. Before that I founded <a href="https://www.partykit.io/">PartyKit</a>,
        which Cloudflare acquired in 2024. Further back, I worked on the React core team, led
        developer tooling for Cloudflare Workers, built social VR at Oculus, and made a fair
        amount of web infrastructure along the way.
      </p>
      <p>
        The thread through all of it is an interest in how a powerful technical idea becomes a
        useful thing: the API, the interface, the explanation, and the bit of taste that makes it
        cohere.
      </p>
      <p>
        This site is less a record of employment and more a working notebook. I write about
        software and systems, but also about tools, judgment, and what happens to a craft when its
        materials change.
      </p>
      <p>
        Away from computers, I like playing guitars, taking long walks, and cooking for people.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 border-t border-dotted border-divider pt-8">
      <SocialList />
    </div>
  </article>
</PageLayout>
